Flow Description
1. Client sends HTTPS request to tenant domain (e.g. tenant-a.com)

2. Request reaches the Virtual IP (VIP) managed by Keepalived (VRRP)

3. VIP forwards traffic to active Envoy node (L4)

4. Envoy performs TLS inspection using SNI (without terminating TLS)

5. Envoy queries xDS Control Plane (if route not cached):
   - Sends SNI (tenant-a.com)
   - Receives cluster endpoint (e.g. 203.0.113.11:443)

6. Envoy forwards TCP connection to target cluster
   - PROXY Protocol v2 header added (preserves client IP)

7. Traffic reaches Tenant Cluster (Traefik DaemonSet on hostNetwork)

8. Traefik:
   - Accepts PROXY Protocol v2
   - Routes based on SNI / Host
   - Forwards to internal Kubernetes Service

9. Application pod receives request
   - Real client IP preserved
   - TLS terminated at application layer (or ingress depending config)


