Global Multi-Cluster Ingress Platform
Envoy + xDS + Traefik (DaemonSet Model)
1. 🎯 Overview

This document describes the design and implementation of a global, multi-cluster ingress platform enabling:

Multi-tenant routing (SNI-based)
Single public entrypoint (VIP)
Dynamic service discovery (xDS)
Cluster isolation with overlapping CIDRs
End-to-end TLS (passthrough)
Preservation of original client IP (PROXY Protocol v2)

The architecture replaces service mesh ingress (e.g. Kuma / Consul) with a lightweight, controllable ingress layer.

2. 🧱 Architecture Components
Tier 1 — Global Entry Point
Keepalived (VRRP)
Provides Virtual IP (VIP): 203.0.113.10
Active/standby failover
Envoy (Edge Data Plane)
Stateless L4 proxy
TLS passthrough
SNI-based routing
xDS-driven dynamic configuration
PROXY Protocol v2 enabled
Control Plane
Custom Go xDS Server
gRPC (ADS)
Dynamic cluster generation
On-demand lookup
Database (PostgreSQL / SQLite)
Mapping: domain → ingress IP:port
Tier 2 — Tenant Clusters
Traefik (DaemonSet, hostNetwork)
Runs on every node
Listens on :443
Accepts PROXY Protocol v2
Routes traffic to Kubernetes services
Applications (Pods)
Receive real client IP
Handle TLS termination (or ingress-level termination)


3. 🔀 Traffic Flow
End-to-End Flow

1. Client → https://tenant-a.com

2. Request → VIP (Keepalived)

3. VIP → Envoy (active node)

4. Envoy:
   - Inspects SNI (tenant-a.com)
   - Queries xDS if not cached

5. xDS Control Plane:
   - Returns cluster endpoint (e.g. 203.0.113.11:443)

6. Envoy:
   - Forwards TCP connection
   - Adds PROXY Protocol v2 header

7. Tenant Cluster:
   - Traefik receives connection on NodeIP:443
   - Parses PROXY header
   - Routes based on SNI/Host

8. Service → Pod

9. Application:
   - Sees original client IP
   - Terminates TLS (or upstream ingress does)

